Minister for Foreign Affairs Shah Mehmood Qureshi Wednesday welcomed thousands of Sikh Yatrees to Pakistan for attending the ceremonies to mark the 552nd birth anniversary of Babu Guru Nanak.
In a tweet on social media platform Twitter, he said, “As ceremonies to mark the 552nd birth anniversary of Baba Guru Nanak Dev Ji begin today at Darbar Kartarpur Sahib, we welcome thousands of Sikh Yatrees from India, Afghanistan, US, UK, Canada and beyond to Pakistan. May Guru Nanak Dev Ji’s message of peace & harmony prevail.”
